---
layout: 'layouts/base.njk'
title: Salt Lake City Tattoo Expo
---

<article>
  <header class="hero-banner">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="container home-grid">
    <section class="section section-dates">
      <div class="section-container">
        <h2>2023</h2>
        <p>
          March
          <span
            >{{ slctattoo.dates[0].date }} -
            {{ slctattoo.dates[slctattoo.dates.length - 1].date }}</span
          >
        </p>
        <p>Salt Palace Convention Center</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-tickets">
      <div class="section-container">
        <a
          href="{{ slctattoo.ticketLink }}"
          class="ticket-button"
          title="24tix.com"
          >Get Your <em>Ticket</em></a
        >

        <p class="text-center">
          $25 per day or $50 for the weekend<br />
          Tickets can be purchased online in advance.<br />
          Cash only at the door.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-about">
      <div class="section-container">
        <p>
          The Salt Lake City International Tattoo Expo is THE premier tattoo
          expo in the western US as well as one of the most prestigious in the
          country. Hosting over 150 of the most talented tattoo artists from
          around the globe as well as artists and vendors. All styles of
          tattooing will be featured. Whether it be American Traditional, Black
          and Gray, Fine Line, Realism, Japanese, we will be showcasing a lineup
          of the best tattoo artists from Utah, the US and around the world in a
          safe, clean and family friendly environment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-news">
      <ul class="post-list">
        {%- for post in collections.posts -%} {% include 'partials/post.njk' %}
        {%- endfor -%}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- <section class="section section-email">
      {% include "partials/email.njk" %}
    </section> -->
  </div>
</article>
